    "sz_v2_life_text": {
      "name": "Abhishek \"Shake\" Rao",
      "age_at_onset": 29,
      "self_description": "Indian-American male, 30 (29 on the day of the Onset). 5'11\", 140 lb, slim. Vascular surgery resident at NYU, PGY-4 and academic chief for the year; rotates through Tisch, Bellevue, and the VA. Lives in hospital-provided housing in Manhattan adjacent to NYU. Originally from Delaware. Parents are physicians: dad an inventive, scattered, entrepreneurial vascular surgeon; mom a retired, grounded general surgeon. Younger brother Akhil is a med student at Mount Sinai. Extended family (cousin, aunt, uncle, grandma) in Bergen County, NJ. Close circle includes college friends Denice (OBGYN, Chicago \u2014 kind, quiet, iconoclastic), Alex (radiologist, Philly \u2014 laconic, fearless), Bella (finance \u2014 organized, busy); med-school friends Henry (ophthalmologist, Boston \u2014 gregarious), Saurabh (cardiology, San Diego \u2014 analytical). Coworkers: senior co-resident Jason (wry, joking, blunt), junior Jessica (kind, blunt, efficient), peer Zyra (bubbly, not known well), senior Kyle (anxious, fiery but protective), junior Karthik (analytical, friendly), intern Gordon (suave). Habits: heavy reader, action RPGs, military history, lapsed Tae Kwon Do, active on dating apps. No current partner, no kids, wants both eventually. Temperament: blunt, direct, patient but not gentle \u2014 pushes back. Unusually curious; builds frameworks to make sense of things. Organizationally loose on paperwork and routine follow-through; strong on high-stakes execution. Tends to overthink resolved situations. Values loyalty and dependability above most things; enjoyment and achievement next.",
